no]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://epidemio.wiv-isp.be/ID/Documents/Covid19/Meest%20recente%20update.pdf|title=COVID-19 - Epidemiologische situatie|date=21 March 2020|website=Sciensano}}</ref> (Belgian Institute for Public Health) }}\n\n[[File:SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in Belgium - Semi-log.jpg|thumb|centre|600 px|[[Semi-log plot|Semi-logarithmic graph]] of the number of confirmed cases, hospitalisations, intensive care cases and deaths in Belgium as of 2020-04-02]]\n[[File:SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in Belgium - Linear.jpg|thumb|centre|600 px|Graph of the number of daily increase of confirmed cases, hospitalisations, intensive care cases and deaths in Belgium as of 2020-04-02]]\n[[File:20200402 Logistic growth COVID-19 Belgium.png|thumb|centre|600 px|[[Logistic function|Logistic growth model]] fit for hospitalized COVID-19 cases in Belgium for data from 14/03/2020 until 02/04/2020. The exponential initial phase has a growth rate of 25.1% and the total number of hospitalized cases stabilises at 9317. Beyond 2 April the curves shown are only a trend according to the logistic growth model, these have an uncertainty range associated to them and should not be seen as a prediction.]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France]] \n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Netherlands]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.info-coronavirus.be/en/ www.info-coronavirus.be], information website from the Belgian government\n* [https://epidemio.wiv-isp.be/ID/Pages/2019-nCoV.aspx New Coronavirus (Disease: COVID-19, Virus: SARS-CoV-2)], epidemiological updates in Belgium - [[Sciensano]]\n* [https://epistat.wiv-isp.be/Covid/ EPISTAT- Infectious Diseases Data Explorations & Visualizations], raw data of the pandemic in Belgium  - [[Sciensano]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Belgium]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Belgium]]